comment_data.body:
@rjw57 Instead of a INSTALL file, I would rather have a script with the following comment at the top:

``` sh
#!/bin/sh
# This script will download, fetch and install dependencies X, Y and Z so that you dont have to waste any time
# If you are the kind of person who feels better by doing everything manually, don't run this script!
```

Just kidding :)

@rjw57 If linking to system libraries by default will make packager maintainers happier, then feel free to commit such a change to the current configuration, but let's leave the bundled subtrees where they are. Those that don't like can just pretend that the 'third-party' isn't there
